snippet.textDisplay: People need to stop projecting their own insecurities on outside factors. There was nothing wrong with the commercial, and by the way, skinny people need toning too. Exercising has more benefits than just weight loss (which by the way, is mainly accomplished through diet). But hey, we live in a society where we're not happy unless we feel offended by something....well, this needs to stop! But how can it stop when anyone who complains for the most ridiculous reasons is given attention, air time, social media exposure and eventually apologies? All nonsense needs to be ignored, and eventually it will go away. As long as the nonsense is being sensationalized and given into, it will continue to exist and will get even worse.

snippet.textDisplay:
Is there anything people won’t be offended by these days? It’s clear in the commercial she wanted it-wouldn’t have used it or posted pics of herself with it otherwise! The fact she has a nice figure to begin with is what I think those that are complaining are actually complaining about. They are looking at it as a weight loss tool not a fitness tool. Something to keep her in shape, better her muscle strength, better her heart health, and get those lungs working to full capacity. All of those things are important NO MATTER what size an individual is, from the thinnest of things, to someone obese. Everyone can always better their heart, lung, muscle health. Plus, doing all that gives off endorphins, so people naturally feel better mentally, gives them more energy.
But yeah, let a few people take this ad and say it’s sexist in some way. Is it sexist to buy the husband a weight machine, bow flex or the like? Or would it only be so if the guy was over or under a certain size? Geez, people just want to find things to complain about, I say we just don’t listen to the ridiculousness. If you give it oxygen, it lives, without it, it’ll eventually die out. ✌️
